From: Zebastjan Johanzen <zebastian.johanzen@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 22 Feb 2026 16:41:53 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 18/25] feat(ingestion): add restartable RAG pipeline with
 separable stages

BREAKING CHANGE / HEAVILY IN DEVELOPMENT - NOT FOR PRODUCTION USE

This commit adds a new restartable RAG ingestion pipeline with the following
features:

- New database tables for state tracking: archon_document_blobs,
  archon_chunks, archon_embedding_sets, archon_embeddings, archon_summaries
- Each pipeline stage (download, chunk, embed, summarize) is now separable
- Full metadata tracking: embedder_id, embedder_version, embedder_config
  for embeddings; summarizer_model_id, prompt_hash, style for summaries
- Checkpointing: each stage has explicit states (pending/in_progress/done/failed)
- Support for multiple embedders and summarization styles per source
- Health check utilities for validating pipeline state

New services:
- services/ingestion/ingestion_state_service.py - State management
- services/ingestion/pipeline_orchestrator.py - Main orchestration
- services/ingestion/embedding_worker.py - Async embedding processor
- services/ingestion/summary_worker.py - Async summarization processor
- services/ingestion/health_check.py - Health validation

Migration: migration/0.1.0/014_add_pipeline_tables.sql

Documentation: docs/ADRs/001-restartable-rag-pipeline.md

The old pipeline remains unchanged for backwards compatibility.
