From 1fd5849bf64b2fb6c97eb2956e2b3349f50e87d1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Zebastjan Johanzen <zebastian.johanzen@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 23 Feb 2026 00:15:25 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 22/25] feat: add pause/resume infrastructure for crawl
 operations (WIP)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Implements foundational pause/resume functionality for web crawl operations
with automatic recovery on Docker restart. Download manager-style controls
with proper state tracking and UI feedback.

## Changes

### Backend - Pause/Resume State Machine
- Add cancellation reason tracking (PAUSED vs STOPPED vs NONE)
- Modify CrawlingService.cancel() to accept reason parameter
- Add CrawlingService.pause() method for explicit pause operations
- Update CancelledError handler to preserve "paused" status
- Pause endpoint now calls orchestration.pause() instead of cancel()

### Backend - Auto-Resume on Restart
- Add ProgressTracker.auto_resume_paused_operations() method
- Server startup now auto-resumes all paused operations
- Operations marked as "paused" after Docker restart automatically continue
- Set source_id early in crawl initialization for pause/resume support

### Backend - Failed Operations Retryable
- Resume endpoint now accepts "failed" status for retry functionality
- Failed operations preserve progress data for recovery

### Frontend - UI Improvements
- Add "Retry" button for failed operations (blue, RotateCw icon)
- Change Resume button icon from StopCircle to Play icon
- Update button visibility logic for paused/failed states
- Visual distinction between Pause (⏹️), Resume (▶️), and Retry (🔄)

## Known Issues

### Critical
- **Cancel button non-functional**: UI does not respond to cancel/stop button
- **Resume doesn't restart crawl**: UI responds to resume button but actual
  crawl operation does not continue (no backend activity detected)
- **Auto-resume may not trigger**: Docker restart shows "Restored" message
  but not always "Auto-resumed" message

### Investigation Needed
- Source_id may still be NULL in some cases despite early initialization
- Cancellation checks (_check_cancellation) may not be frequent enough
  during long-running operations like discovery or initial page crawling
- Active orchestration registry may not properly track paused operations

## Testing Status
- ✅ Pause button changes status to "paused" in database
- ✅ UI shows correct badges (Paused/Cancelled/Failed)
- ✅ Resume button appears for paused operations
- ❌ Resume does not actually restart crawl
- ❌ Cancel button does not stop operations
- ⚠️  Auto-resume inconsistent on Docker restart

## Next Steps
1. Debug why resume endpoint doesn't restart crawl service
2. Fix cancel button to properly stop operations
3. Ensure _check_cancellation() called frequently in all crawl stages
4. Add more detailed logging for pause/resume/cancel operations
5. Verify source_id persistence across pause/resume cycles

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
