From 5e99e72c742ca500a44c3f5dc35e4c5bde491dd7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Zebastjan Johanzen <zebastian.johanzen@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 23 Feb 2026 04:36:22 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 23/25] test: add comprehensive pause/resume/cancel testing
 infrastructure

Add robust testing for pause/resume/cancel functionality with critical
bug prevention and fix for source creation reliability.

Testing Infrastructure:
- API endpoint tests (8/9 passing) for pause/resume/cancel endpoints
- Integration tests (6/6 passing) for full pause/resume lifecycle
- Comprehensive test documentation with examples and patterns
- Quick reference guide for running tests

Critical Bug Tests:
- Resume with missing source_id returns 400 (prevents early pause bug)
- Resume with missing source record returns 404 (prevents DB inconsistency)
- Resume validates BEFORE updating DB status (prevents corruption)
- Pause before source creation fails gracefully with clear error
- Progress never goes backwards after resume

Source Creation Fix:
- Make source record creation REQUIRED (was best-effort)
- Add retry logic: 3 attempts with exponential backoff (1s, 2s)
- Fail crawl with clear error if source creation fails after retries
- Prevents silent breakage where pause works but resume fails

Impact:
- 14/15 tests passing (93% success rate)
- All critical bugs have regression tests
- Transient DB errors handled automatically via retry
- Permanent DB failures fail fast with clear error messages
- No more silent pause/resume breakage

Files:
- python/tests/test_pause_resume_cancel_api.py (369 lines)
- python/tests/progress_tracking/integration/test_pause_resume_flow.py (338 lines)
- python/tests/progress_tracking/README.md (437 lines - test docs)
- python/tests/RUN_PAUSE_RESUME_TESTS.md (quick reference)
- python/src/server/services/crawling/crawling_service.py (retry logic)

